  "prompt": "I am in Tier 2 general visa for 3 years, I am in It. most of client not choosing the Tier 2 general visa, they are not interested in Contract offer?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why clients may be hesitant to choose Tier 2 General visa candidates:\n\n1. Cost and Administrative Burden\n- Sponsorship costs are high\n- Complex immigration paperwork\n- Additional compliance requirements\n- Paying visa fees and healthcare surcharge\n\n2. Recruitment Challenges\n- Limited understanding of Tier 2 visa process\n- Preference for local candidates\n- Perceived complexity of hiring international workers\n\n3. Recruitment Restrictions\n- Some companies have strict hiring policies\n- Budget constraints\n- Limited roles suitable for international candidates\n\n4. Potential Solutions\n- Highlight unique skills and expertise\n- Demonstrate value proposition\n- Network actively\n- Consider contract or freelance roles initially\n- Build professional reputation\n- Specialize in niche technologies\n- Obtain certifications\n- Improve communication skills\n- Be flexible with job requirements\n\n5. Alternative Strategies\n- Look for sponsor-friendly companies\n- Target multinational corporations\n- Explore IT consulting firms\n- Consider startups\n- Utilize professional networking platforms\n- Attend industry events\n- Leverage recruitment agencies specializing in international placements\n\n6. Market Research\n- Understand current recruitment trends\n- Analyze job market demands\n- Identify skills in high demand\n\nPersistence and strategic approach are key to finding suitable opportunities.",
